docs.abstract: Bernie Sanders’s advisers and allies want him to get personal with voters as he struggles in the 2020 race. But that isn’t his style.
docs.snippet: Bernie Sanders’s advisers and allies want him to get personal with voters as he struggles in the 2020 race. But that isn’t his style.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Senator Bernie Sanders brought his presidential campaign to Pittsburgh earlier this year, he quietly added a poignant stop to his schedule: a visit to the Tree of Life synagogue, where 11 congregants were killed in an anti-Semitic shooting last fall.

headline.main: Why Sanders Wanted His Meeting With a Rabbi Kept Secret
headline.print_headline: Sanders Struggles to Connect, but Refuses to Run on Personality

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Amy McGrath, a retired Marine lieutenant colonel and combat pilot whose star power in the Democratic Party in 2018 failed to capture her a House seat in Kentucky, announced Tuesday that she would seek to challenge Senator Mitch McConnell, the Republican majority leader, in 2020.

headline.main: Amy McGrath Opens Campaign to Oust Mitch McConnell in Kentucky
headline.print_headline: Marine Pilot Begins Bid To Oppose  McConnell

docs.abstract: The former vice president and his wife made millions through speeches and books after he left office, according to tax returns his campaign released Tuesday.
docs.snippet: The former vice president and his wife made millions through speeches and books after he left office, according to tax returns his campaign released Tuesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Over his long career in politics, Joseph R. Biden Jr. established his everyman bona fides by citing his status as the poorest member of the Senate and referring to himself as “Middle-Class Joe.” But in the first two years after leaving office, Mr. Biden substantially improved his financial fortunes, earning more than $15 million, according to tax returns his campaign released Tuesday.

headline.main: Joe Biden’s Tax Returns Show More Than $15 Million in Income After 2016
headline.print_headline: Bidens Earned $15 Million After 2016, Challenging ‘Middle-Class Joe’ Image

docs.lead_paragraph: On Sunday, President Trump used a well-worn racist trope to attack progressive Democrats who are frequent objects of his ire. “Why don’t they go back and help fix the totally broken and crime infested places from which they came,” Mr. Trump said in one of a series of posts on Twitter.

headline.main: Have You Been Told to ‘Go Back’ to Your Country Even Though You Are American? Tell Us About It.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont offered a vigorous defense of the democratic socialism that has defined his five decades in political life on Wednesday, while tying his presidential campaign to the legacies of Franklin D. Roosevelt and Martin Luther King Jr.

docs.lead_paragraph: DAVENPORT, Iowa — President Trump and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. repeatedly ripped into each other on Tuesday as unfit to lead the country as they both traveled to the battleground state of Iowa, giving voters a preview of what a general election matchup between the two men might look like.

headline.main: Trump and Biden Get Personal in Iowa Skirmish

docs.lead_paragraph: The behind-the-scenes competition for Wall Street money in the 2020 presidential race is reaching a fevered peak this week as no less than nine Democrats are holding New York fund-raisers in a span of nine days, racing ahead of a June 30 filing deadline when they must disclose their latest financial hauls.

headline.main: Wall Street Donors Are Swooning for Mayor Pete. (They Like Biden and Harris, Too.)
